Destutt de Tracy’s Treatise on Political Economy, is finally published. Salma Hale visits Monticello and describes Jefferson’s views on food, wine, and religion. In acknowledging an oration by Mordecai M. Noah, Jefferson remarks that the suffering of members of the Jewish faith "has furnished a remarkable proof of the universal spirit of religious intolerance." He receives long discussions of occult science and the nature of light by Robert Miller and Gabriel Crane. Abigail Adams dies, and Jefferson assures John Adams that their own demise will result in “an ecstatic meeting with the friends we have loved & lost and whom we shall still love and never lose again.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPresidentszUnited StatesvArchives. 0aPresidentszUnited StatesvCorrespondence. 7aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century.2bisacsh  aA History of England.  aAaron Burr.  aAbraham Gottlob Werner.  aAdelbert von Chamisso.  aAdjournment.  aAlbert Gallatin.  aAmerican Antiquarian Society.  aAmerican Colonization Society.  aAn Essay on the Principle of Population.  aAnnals (Tacitus).  aArticles of Confederation.  aBattle of White Plains.  aBattles of Saratoga.  aBenjamin Vaughan.  aBill of lading.  aBushrod Washington.  aButton Gwinnett.  aCalculation.  aCato the Elder.  aCharles Cotesworth Pinckney.  aChemical Society.  aCollege of William & Mary.  aConfucius.  aConsideration.  aContinental Army.  aDartmouth College.  aDartmouth University.  aDeWitt Clinton.  aDemocritus.  aDormitory.  aDutch West India Company.  aEdward Coles.  aEdward Rutledge.  aFuture History (Heinlein).  aGeorge Ticknor.  aGeorge Wythe.  aGrammar school.  aHarvard University.  aHenry Dearborn.  aHis Family.  aI Wish (manhwa).  aInstitution.  aInvoice.  aJ. (newspaper).